getAttributeNames

public Set<String> getAttributeNames(String pattern)
Gets an enumeration of the session attributes that match a pattern. For example, if the pattern is "form-.*", will return attributes with keys "form-11", "form-12", "form-" and so on.

Returns:
Set of String. Client keeps the set and can iterate over it.

getAttributes

public Set<Map.Entry<String,Object>> getAttributes()
Gets the all the attributes of the session. Like Map.entrySet(), but the set is a copy: Client can add and remove session attributes while iterating over the result of this method.

Returns:
Set of Map.Entry. Client must not call setKey or setValue, that would affect the current session attributes.
